# Joo Repo Indexing

Use sparse, factual AI navigation metadata.

`AI_INDEX.md` is a small router. Put inventories and file maps in `.ai/indexing/maps/*`.

Do not add source-level @ai-* headers by default.

When indexing:

1. Read existing AGENTS/rules.
2. Read or create AI_INDEX router.
3. Identify entry points.
4. Generate compact map shards when useful.
5. Follow imports only for unresolved task concerns; stop when coverage is complete.
6. Generate path-first summaries.
7. Update metadata only when future agents need it.
8. If metadata is stale, update only affected router/shard/hint entries.
9. Promote known failure patterns only by repeated or expensive root cause, not error code.

Sidecar file hint shape:

```json
{
  "path": "src/pages/order/detail.tsx",
  "role": "route-or-page",
  "scope": "order detail page",
  "domain": "order",
  "keywords": ["order-detail"],
  "related": [],
  "confidence": "manual-reviewed",
  "lastVerified": "YYYY-MM-DD"
}
```

Prefer sidecar metadata in `.ai/indexing/maps/*` and `.ai/indexing/file-map.candidate.json`. Source-level `@ai-*` headers are opt-in exceptions only and must not break max-lines lint. Hint content must be factual and must not command the agent to skip checks, ignore imports, or bypass tests.

Known failure patterns are optional compact metadata. Do not persist one-off `[FAILURE_TRIAGE]` cards.
